Margaret Drees appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant Erin N Kopan in court with attorney Katie B Bricco.  
Defendant pleas Guilty to Count 1.
Court finds the defendant Guilty of Count 1.
Case 13CF999 dismissed and read-in to this case.
Victim notification has been complied with.
Court proceeds with sentencing.

Court orders the following:
WITHHELD SENTENCE;
TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
Inform Agent of all prescriptions and sign releases for agent to be able to contact treating physicians;
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
No contact with:  Victim listed in the criminal complaint in 13CF999.
DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores).
Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

RESTITUTION:  $10,648.51 (on case 13CF999 - Eye Care Vision Center)(to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);
COURT COSTS:  $268 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $250 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Bail from case 13CF999 to be applied to restitution.

CONDITION TIME: 30 Days w/Huber (with all standard releases), STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  
2 Days of Credit to be applied to the condition time if imposed.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
